data.name: AddVerbDescription
data.value: Adds a resource to a container, or attaches an item to another item

data.name: ApproveVerbDescription
data.value: Confirms or agrees to the status of a resource or process

data.name: AssertVerbDescription
data.value: Affirms the state of a resource

data.name: BackupVerbDescription
data.value: Stores data by replicating it

data.name: BlockVerbDescription
data.value: Restricts access to a resource

data.name: BuildVerbDescription
data.value: Creates an artifact (usually a binary or document) out of some set of input files (usually source code or declarative documents)

data.name: CheckpointVerbDescription
data.value: Creates a snapshot of the current state of the data or of its configuration

data.name: ClearVerbDescription
data.value: Removes all the resources from a container but does not delete the container

data.name: CloseVerbDescription
data.value: Changes the state of a resource to make it inaccessible, unavailable, or unusable

data.name: CompareVerbDescription
data.value: Evaluates the data from one resource against the data from another resource

data.name: CompleteVerbDescription
data.value: Concludes an operation

data.name: CompressVerbDescription
data.value: Compacts the data of a resource

data.name: ConfirmVerbDescription
data.value: Acknowledges, verifies, or validates the state of a resource or process

data.name: ConnectVerbDescription
data.value: Creates a link between a source and a destination

data.name: ConvertVerbDescription
data.value: Changes the data from one representation to another when the cmdlet supports bidirectional conversion or when the cmdlet supports conversion between multiple data types

data.name: ConvertFromVerbDescription
data.value: Converts one primary type of input (the cmdlet noun indicates the input) to one or more supported output types

data.name: ConvertToVerbDescription
data.value: Converts from one or more types of input to a primary output type (the cmdlet noun indicates the output type)

data.name: CopyVerbDescription
data.value: Copies a resource to another name or to another container

data.name: DebugVerbDescription
data.value: Examines a resource to diagnose operational problems

data.name: DenyVerbDescription
data.value: Refuses, objects, blocks, or opposes the state of a resource or process

data.name: DeployVerbDescription
data.value: Sends an application, website, or solution to a remote target[s] in such a way that a consumer of that solution can access it after deployment is complete

data.name: DisableVerbDescription
data.value: Configures a resource to an unavailable or inactive state

data.name: DisconnectVerbDescription
data.value: Breaks the link between a source and a destination

data.name: DismountVerbDescription
data.value: Detaches a named entity from a location

data.name: EditVerbDescription
data.value: Modifies existing data by adding or removing content

data.name: EnableVerbDescription
data.value: Configures a resource to an available or active state

data.name: EnterVerbDescription
data.value: Specifies an action that allows the user to move into a resource

data.name: ExitVerbDescription
data.value: Sets the current environment or context to the most recently used context

data.name: ExpandVerbDescription
data.value: Restores the data of a resource that has been compressed to its original state

data.name: ExportVerbDescription
data.value: Encapsulates the primary input into a persistent data store, such as a file, or into an interchange format

data.name: FindVerbDescription
data.value: Looks for an object in a container that is unknown, implied, optional, or specified

data.name: FormatVerbDescription
data.value: Arranges objects in a specified form or layout

data.name: GetVerbDescription
data.value: Specifies an action that retrieves a resource

data.name: GrantVerbDescription
data.value: Allows access to a resource

data.name: GroupVerbDescription
data.value: Arranges or associates one or more resources

data.name: HideVerbDescription
data.value: Makes a resource undetectable

data.name: ImportVerbDescription
data.value: Creates a resource from data that is stored in a persistent data store (such as a file) or in an interchange format

data.name: InitializeVerbDescription
data.value: Prepares a resource for use, and sets it to a default state

data.name: InstallVerbDescription
data.value: Places a resource in a location, and optionally initializes it

data.name: InvokeVerbDescription
data.value: Performs an action, such as running a command or a method

data.name: JoinVerbDescription
data.value: Combines resources into one resource

data.name: LimitVerbDescription
data.value: Applies constraints to a resource

data.name: LockVerbDescription
data.value: Secures a resource

data.name: MeasureVerbDescription
data.value: Identifies resources that are consumed by a specified operation, or retrieves statistics about a resource

data.name: MergeVerbDescription
data.value: Creates a single resource from multiple resources

data.name: MountVerbDescription
data.value: Attaches a named entity to a location

data.name: MoveVerbDescription
data.value: Moves a resource from one location to another

data.name: NewVerbDescription
data.value: Creates a resource

data.name: OpenVerbDescription
data.value: Changes the state of a resource to make it accessible, available, or usable

data.name: OptimizeVerbDescription
data.value: Increases the effectiveness of a resource

data.name: OutVerbDescription
data.value: Sends data out of the environment

data.name: PingVerbDescription
data.value: Use the Test verb

data.name: PopVerbDescription
data.value: Removes an item from the top of a stack

data.name: ProtectVerbDescription
data.value: Safeguards a resource from attack or loss

data.name: PublishVerbDescription
data.value: Makes a resource available to others

data.name: PushVerbDescription
data.value: Adds an item to the top of a stack

data.name: ReadVerbDescription
data.value: Acquires information from a source

data.name: ReceiveVerbDescription
data.value: Accepts information sent from a source

data.name: RedoVerbDescription
data.value: Resets a resource to the state that was undone

data.name: RegisterVerbDescription
data.value: Creates an entry for a resource in a repository such as a database

data.name: RemoveVerbDescription
data.value: Deletes a resource from a container

data.name: RenameVerbDescription
data.value: Changes the name of a resource

data.name: RepairVerbDescription
data.value: Restores a resource to a usable condition

data.name: RequestVerbDescription
data.value: Asks for a resource or asks for permissions

data.name: ResetVerbDescription
data.value: Sets a resource back to its original state

data.name: ResizeVerbDescription
data.value: Changes the size of a resource

data.name: ResolveVerbDescription
data.value: Maps a shorthand representation of a resource to a more complete representation

data.name: RestartVerbDescription
data.value: Stops an operation and then starts it again

data.name: RestoreVerbDescription
data.value: Sets a resource to a predefined state, such as a state set by Checkpoint

data.name: ResumeVerbDescription
data.value: Starts an operation that has been suspended

data.name: RevokeVerbDescription
data.value: Specifies an action that does not allow access to a resource

data.name: SaveVerbDescription
data.value: Preserves data to avoid loss

data.name: SearchVerbDescription
data.value: Creates a reference to a resource in a container

data.name: SelectVerbDescription
data.value: Locates a resource in a container

data.name: SendVerbDescription
data.value: Delivers information to a destination

data.name: SetVerbDescription
data.value: Replaces data on an existing resource or creates a resource that contains some data

data.name: ShowVerbDescription
data.value: Makes a resource visible to the user

data.name: SyncVerbDescription
data.value: Assures that two or more resources are in the same state

data.name: SkipVerbDescription
data.value: Bypasses one or more resources or points in a sequence

data.name: SplitVerbDescription
data.value: Separates parts of a resource

data.name: StartVerbDescription
data.value: Initiates an operation

data.name: StepVerbDescription
data.value: Moves to the next point or resource in a sequence

data.name: StopVerbDescription
data.value: Discontinues an activity

data.name: SubmitVerbDescription
data.value: Presents a resource for approval

data.name: SuspendVerbDescription
data.value: Pauses an activity

data.name: SwitchVerbDescription
data.value: Specifies an action that alternates between two resources, such as to change between two locations, responsibilities, or states

data.name: TestVerbDescription
data.value: Verifies the operation or consistency of a resource

data.name: TraceVerbDescription
data.value: Tracks the activities of a resource

data.name: UnblockVerbDescription
data.value: Removes restrictions to a resource

data.name: UndoVerbDescription
data.value: Sets a resource to its previous state

data.name: UninstallVerbDescription
data.value: Removes a resource from an indicated location

data.name: UnlockVerbDescription
data.value: Releases a resource that was locked

data.name: UnprotectVerbDescription
data.value: Removes safeguards from a resource that were added to prevent it from attack or loss

data.name: UnpublishVerbDescription
data.value: Makes a resource unavailable to others

data.name: UnregisterVerbDescription
data.value: Removes the entry for a resource from a repository

data.name: UpdateVerbDescription
data.value: Brings a resource up-to-date to maintain its state, accuracy, conformance, or compliance

data.name: UseVerbDescription
data.value: Uses or includes a resource to do something

data.name: WaitVerbDescription
data.value: Pauses an operation until a specified event occurs

data.name: WatchVerbDescription
data.value: Continually inspects or monitors a resource for changes

data.name: WriteVerbDescription
data.value: Adds information to a target
